{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/videos/recipes/foolproof-kohakutou-japanese-rock-candy","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<figure class=\"ingredients\" markdown=\"1\">\n<h3 id=\"kohakatou\"><a href=\"#kohakatou\" aria-label=\"kohakatou permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Kohakatou</h3>\n<p>(Makes 1 1/2 trays of rock candy)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>2 cups water</li>\n<li>15 grams agar agar (Thai Brand)</li>\n<li>4 cups sugar</li>\n<li>flavoring, optional</li>\n<li>food coloring, optional</li>\n</ul>\n</figure>\n<figure class=\"directions\" markdown=\"1\">\n<h3 id=\"directions\"><a href=\"#directions\" aria-label=\"directions permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Directions</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Bring water and agar to a boil.  Once agar is dissolved, add in the sugar.</li>\n<li>Place a candy thermometer in the mix and cook mixture over medium heat until mixture reaches 230 degrees Fahrenheit.</li>\n<li>Pour into a greased 13x9-inch dish.</li>\n<li>Let mixture set for at least 4 hours.</li>\n<li>Cut or rip the set agar apart and place on parchment.</li>\n<li>Let candies sit for 3-4 days until a sugar crust develops on all sides.</li>\n<li>\n<p>Candy is then ready for eating or packaging.</p>\n</figure>\n</li>\n</ol>","timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"Kohakatou (Makes 1 1/2 trays of rock candy) 2 cups water 15 grams agar agar (Thai Brand) 4 cups sugar flavoring, optional food coloringâ€¦","frontmatter":{"title":"Foolproof Kohakutou - Japanese Rock Candy","image":{"feature":{"publicURL":"/static/385-1-e5af00553f766ec255c3aad7013ef544.jpg","childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.5,"src":"/static/e5af00553f766ec255c3aad7013ef544/b17c1/385-1.jpg","srcSet":"/static/e5af00553f766ec255c3aad7013ef544/00e5e/385-1.jpg 200w,\n/static/e5af00553f766ec255c3aad7013ef544/1a903/385-1.jpg 400w,\n/static/e5af00553f766ec255c3aad7013ef544/b17c1/385-1.jpg 800w,\n/static/e5af00553f766ec255c3aad7013ef544/2f073/385-1.jpg 1200w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}}},"feature_video":"https://www.youtube.com/embed/31iaIy3opP8","date":"2018-01-30","categories":["videos","recipes"],"tags":["videos","vegan","kohakutou","rock candy","japan"]},"fields":{"slug":"/videos/recipes/foolproof-kohakutou-japanese-rock-candy","date":"2018-01-30T00:00:00.000Z"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/videos/recipes/foolproof-kohakutou-japanese-rock-candy","nextslug":"/videos/blog/best-vegan-restaurants-in-london","prevslug":"/videos/blog/best-vegan-restaurants-in-bangkok-thailand-and-chiangrai"}}}